SIMPLE: spanner
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: spanner
<hw>span"ner</hw> <pr>(sp⟦acr⟧n"n⟦etil⟧r)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<sn>1.</sn> <def>One who, or that which, spans.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>The lock of a fusee or carbine; also, the fusee or
carbine itself.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>An iron instrument having a jaw to fit a nut or the
head of a bolt, and used as a lever to turn it with; a wrench;
specifically, a wrench for unscrewing or tightening the couplings of
hose.</def> <mark>[Chiefly British usage]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>4.</sn> <pluf>pl.</pluf> <def>A contrivance in some of the
earlier steam engines for moving the valves for the alternate admission
and shutting off of the steam.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>span-new</ent>⟦br⟧
